# web-kit → tenant-runtime wiring (grafik grid, M2-A5). Copy to .env.local for local dev.

# Base URL of the tenant-runtime (NestJS) API the /api/grafik/* + /api/employees proxies forward to.
# Local dev default (used when unset): http://localhost:3001
# On the docker-compose network use the service name:
#   TENANT_RUNTIME_URL=http://tenant-runtime:3001
TENANT_RUNTIME_URL=http://localhost:3001

# Server-only Keycloak direct-grant provider (lib/keycloak-token.ts). When ALL FOUR vars are set, the
# proxy mints its own tenant-runtime bearer, caches it in module scope, and auto-refreshes before the
# ~300s expiry — no static token needed. Precedence: caller Authorization header → hrobot_token cookie
# → minted Keycloak token (these vars) → legacy TENANT_RUNTIME_DEV_TOKEN → 401. If any var is unset the
# provider is a no-op and we fall through. Keep these ONLY in a gitignored .env.local — NEVER commit
# real creds (RODO/security).
# KEYCLOAK_TOKEN_URL=http://localhost:8081/realms/hrobot-staging/protocol/openid-connect/token
# KEYCLOAK_CLIENT_ID=hrobot-web
# KEYCLOAK_USERNAME=demo
# KEYCLOAK_PASSWORD=

# OPTIONAL dev/UAT fallback bearer token forwarded to tenant-runtime when the request carries no
# Authorization header, no `hrobot_token` cookie, and no KEYCLOAK_* creds. web-kit has no Keycloak/
# Auth.js login flow yet (login-form.tsx is a mock), so set this to a valid Keycloak JWT to exercise
# the live round-trip. Leave unset in any shared/hosted environment — the proxy returns 401 rather
# than using a token.
# TENANT_RUNTIME_DEV_TOKEN=
